The heritage listed "Christians Minde Retreat" is situated on the eastern coast of Australia and is bordered by the Booderee National Park, on the shores of Sussex Inlet, in Jervis Bay Territory.

The property will be sold on a vacant possession basis.

'Christians Minde' is a rustic style guest house, which was erected in 1896 by the Ellmoos family and is set on 11 acres of grounds in Jervis Bay Territory.  A 50m stretch of water separates the Christians Minde retreat from the main town of Sussex Inlet.

Christians Minde retreat was the first guest house on the coast south between Sydney and Eden.  In the late 1940's the guest house was converted into self-contained units.  Today the property offers self-contained units situated on the shores of Sussex Inlet.

Accommodation provides for 5 units (guest houses) and a residence, undercover BBQ facilities, communal laundry, a common room with TV, the cemetery, and outbuildings including boat sheds, and other service buildings located on the waters edge, including Christians Minde, the jetty and boathouse.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The sale presents an opportunity to acquire a well-established village in a sought-after Tweed Coast location, 38km from the Gold Coast and 110km from Brisbane.

The village has existing approval for 147 sites in total consisting of 105 long term sites and 42 short term sites. The established park is currently run under management, and facilities include swimming pool, picnic areas and outdoor communal recreation space.

The offering provides secure income, with the opportunity to re-activate vacant tourism sites to generate additional short stay income – or investigate the potential to convert these to permanent sites (STCA).

Please note this is part of a select portfolio sale by Hometown Australia Communities. If you would like further information on the other properties, please contact the exclusive agent.
